record_data.record_plain_text: Rate Schedule No. 1 Formula Rate Implementation Protocols of Transource Missouri, LLC (Attachment H-___) Tariff Submitter: Transource Missouri, LLC FERC Tariff Program Name: FERC FPA Electronic Tariff Tariff Title: TMO Tariff Database Tariff Record Proposed Effective Date: October 30, 2012 Tariff Record Title: Protocols Option Code: A Page1of16 APPENDIX B TRANSOURCE MISSOURI, LLC FORMULA RATE IMPLEMENTATION PROTOCOLS The formula rate template ( Template ) and these Formula Rate Implementation Protocols ( Protocols ) together comprise the filed rate ( Formula Rate ) of Transource Missouri, LLC ( Transource Missouri ) for transmission revenue requirement determinations under the Southwest Power Pool ( SPP ) Open Access Transmission Tariff ( OATT ). Transource Missouri shall follow the instructions specified in the Formula Rate to calculate annually its net revenue requirement, as set forth at page 1, line 4 of the Template ( Net Revenue Requirement ). The project-specific net revenue requirements determined under the Formula Rate are up to rates, i.e., ceiling rates, and permit Transource Missouri to discount the revenue requirement for a future project to the extent necessary to reflect the result of any competitive bidding on such a project. The Net Revenue Requirement (page 1, line 4 of the Template) shall be determined for January 1 to December 31 of a given calendar year (the Rate Year ). The Formula Rate shall become effective for recovery of Transource Missouri s Net Revenue Requirement upon the effective date for incorporation into the SPP OATT through an appropriate filing with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ( FERC or Commission ) under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act ( FPA ). Section 1. Annual Projection a. No later than September 30 preceding the first Rate Year, and each subsequent Rate Year, Transource Missouri shall determine its projected Net Revenue Page2of16 Requirement for the upcoming Rate Year in accordance with Transource Missouri s Formula Rate ( Annual Projection ). The Annual Projection shall include the True-up Adjustment described and defined in Section 2 below, if applicable. Transource Missouri shall cause an electronic version of the Annual Projection to be posted in both a Portable Document Format and fully-functioning Excel file at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website. Such posting shall include (i) all inputs in sufficient detail to identify the components of Transource Missouri s projected Net Revenue Requirement, and (ii) explanations of the bases for the projections and input data. If the date for making such posting of the Annual Projection should fall on a weekend or a holiday recognized by FERC, then the posting shall be made no later than the next business day. Transource Missouri shall electronically serve each Annual Projection upon the Service List.1 b. To the extent Transource Missouri agrees to make changes in the Annual Projection for a given Rate Year, such revised Annual Projection shall be promptly posted at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website and a link to the website shall be electronically served upon the Service List. Changes posted prior to November 30 of the preceding Rate Year, or the next business day if November 30 is not a business day (or such later date as can be accommodated under SPP s billing practices), shall be reflected in the Annual Projection for the 1 As used in these protocols, Service List shall mean (i) the email list of SPP OATT Transmission Customers maintained by the SPP; (ii) any state regulatory agency with rate jurisdiction over a public utility located within the SPP footprint; and (iii) any consumer advocate agency authorized by state law to review and contest the rates for any such public utility, provided such consumer advocate agency requests to be placed on the Service List and provides an e-mail address to Transource Missouri. Page3of16 Rate Year; changes posted after that date will be reflected, as appropriate, in the True-up Adjustment for the Rate Year. c. The Annual Projection, including the True-Up Adjustment, for each Rate Year shall be subject to review, challenge, true-up and refunds or surcharges with interest, to the extent and in the manner provided in these Protocols. Section 2. True-up Adjustment Transource Missouri will calculate the amount of under- or over-collection of its actual Net Revenue Requirement during the preceding Rate Year ( True-up Adjustment ) after the FERC Form No. 1 data for that Rate Year has been filed with the Commission. The True-up Adjustment shall be the sum of components a and b, determined in the following manner: a. Transource Missouri s projected Net Revenue Requirement collected during the previous Rate Year2 will be compared to Transource Missouri s actual Net Revenue Requirement for the previous Rate Year calculated in accordance with Transource Missouri s Formula Rate and based upon (i) Transource Missouri s FERC Form No. 1 for that same Rate Year, (ii) any FERC orders specifically applicable to Transource Missouri s calculation of its annual revenue requirement, (iii) the books and records of Transource Missouri (which shall be maintained consistent with the FERC Uniform System of Accounts ( USoA )), (iv) FERC accounting policies and practices applicable to the calculation of annual revenue 2 If the initial year of this rate schedule is a partial year, the initial projected Net Revenue Requirement will be divided by the number of months the Formula Rate is in effect to calculate the monthly projected cost of service to be collected each month of the first year. Similarly, the actual Net Revenue Requirement will be divided by the number of months the rate is in effect to calculate the actual cost of service to be collected each month of the first year. The first True-up Adjustment will compare the projected Net Revenue Requirement billed and the actual Net Revenue Requirement for that initial Rate Year. Page4of16 requirements under formula rates, and (v) any aspects of the SPP OATT Governing Documents that apply to the calculation of annual revenue requirements under individual transmission owner formula rates, 3 to determine any over- or under-recovery ( True-up Adjustment Over/Under Recovery ). Transource Missouri will include a variance analysis of, at minimum, actual revenue requirement components of rate base, operating and maintenance expenses, depreciation expense, taxes, return on rate base, and revenue credits as compared to the corresponding components in the projected revenue requirement that was calculated for the prior Rate Year with an explanation of material changes. b. Interest on any True-up Adjustment Over/Under Recovery of the actual Net Revenue Requirement shall be calculated in accordance with the Formula Rate true-up worksheet. Section 3. Annual Update a. On or before June 30 following each Rate Year, Transource Missouri shall calculate its actual Net Revenue Requirement and the True-up Adjustment as described in Section 2 ( Annual Update ) for such Rate Year, and shall cause such Annual Update to be posted, in both a Portable Document Format and fully- functioning Excel format containing the populated template for that year s update, at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website, and electronically 3 SPP OATT Governing Documents include the SPP OATT, Bylaws, Criteria, and Membership Agreements. Page5of16 serve a link to the website on the Service List. In addition, the Annual Update shall be contemporaneously submitted as an informational filing with the FERC. b. If the date for making the Annual Update posting should fall on a weekend or a holiday recognized by the FERC, then the posting shall be due on the next business day. c. The date on which the last of the events listed in Section 3.a or 3.b occurs shall be that year s Publication Date. d. Together with the posting of the Annual Update, Transource Missouri shall cause to be posted on the SPP website the time, date and location for a stakeholder meeting with (i) any Eligible Customer under the SPP OATT; (ii) any regulatory agency with rate jurisdiction over a public utility located within the SPP footprint; (iii) any consumer advocate authorized by state law to review and contest the rates for any such public utility, or (iv) any party with standing under FPA Section 205 or 206 (collectively, "Interested Persons") in order for Transource Missouri to explain its Annual Update and to provide Interested Persons an opportunity to seek information and clarifications regarding the Annual Update ( Stakeholder Meeting ). The Stakeholder Meeting shall be held no less than twenty (20) business days and no more than thirty (30) business days after June 30. e. The Annual Update for the Rate Year: Page6of16 (i) Shall provide, via the Formula Rate worksheets, sufficiently detailed supporting documentation for data (and all adjustments thereto or allocations thereof) used in the Formula Rate that are not stated in the FERC Form No. 1;4 (ii) Shall provide notice of changes in Transource Missouri s accounting policies and practices from those in effect for the calendar year upon which the immediately preceding Annual Update was based that affect the Formula Rate or calculation of the Annual Update ( Accounting Change(s) ). Such notice shall include (i) those changes that, in Transource Missouri s reasonable judgment, could impact the Formula Rate or the calculations under the Formula Rate within the next three years; (ii) any changes in the SPP OATT from the provisions of the SPP OATT in effect during the calendar year upon which the most recent ATRR was based and that, in Transource Missouri s reasonable judgment, could impact the Formula Rate or the calculations under the Formula Rate within the next three years; and (iii) any change, and the dollar value of the change, in the classification of any transmission facility under Attachment AI of the SPP OATT (including the costs of any reclassified facility) that 4 It is the intent of the Formula Rate, including the supporting explanations and allocations described therein, that each input to the Formula Rate for purposes of determining the actual Net Revenue Requirement for a given Rate Year will be either taken directly from the FERC Form No. 1 or reconcilable to the FERC Form No. 1 by the application of clearly identified and supported information. If the referenced form is superseded, the successor form(s) shall be utilized and supplemented as necessary to provide equivalent information as that provided in the superseded form. If the referenced form is discontinued, equivalent information as that provided in the discontinued form shall be utilized. Page7of16 Transource Missouri has made in the applicable True-Up Adjustment or Annual Update. (iii) Shall be subject to review and challenge in accordance with the procedures set forth in Sections 4, 5, and 6 of these Protocols. (iv) Shall be subject to review and challenge in accordance with the procedures set forth in these Protocols with respect to the prudence of any costs and expenditures included for recovery in the Annual Update; provided, however, that nothing in these Protocols is intended to modify the Commission s applicable precedent with respect to the burden of going forward or burden of proof under formula rates in such prudence challenges; and (v) Shall not seek to modify the Formula Rate and shall not be subject to challenge by any Interested Person seeking to modify the Formula Rate. (i.e., any modifications to the Formula Rate will require, as applicable, an FPA Section 205 or Section 206 filing or initiation of a Section 206 investigation). f. The following Formula Rate inputs shall be stated values to be used in the Formula Rate until changed pursuant to an FPA Section 205 or 206 proceeding: (i) rate of return on common equity ( ROE ); (ii) Post-Employment Benefits other than Pensions pursuant to Statement of Financial Accounting Standards No. 106, Employers Accounting for Postretirement Benefits Other Than Page8of16 Pensions ( PBOP ) charges; and (iii) the depreciation and/or amortization rates as set forth in Attachment 9 to the Formula Rate template. g. Example Timeline for 2015 Annual Update: On or before September 30, 2013, Transource Missouri will determine the projected Net Revenue Requirement for the 2014 Rate Year, which is expected to be the first year that costs are recovered from SPP customers under the Formula Rate. Transource Missouri will post the Annual Projection for the 2014 Rate Year in accordance with Section 1 above. Transource Missouri will not determine a True-up Adjustment or post an Annual Update on August 1, 2014 if no costs have been recovered under the Formula Rate during 2013. On or before September 30, 2014, Transource Missouri will post the Annual Projection for the 2015 Rate Year. On or before August 1, 2015, Transource Missouri will post its first Annual Update, consisting of the True-up Adjustment for the 2014 Rate Year determined pursuant to Section 2 above. Such True-up Adjustment will be reflected in the Annual Projection of the Net Revenue Requirement for the 2016 Rate Year posted on or before September 30, 2015. The Annual Update posted August 1, 2015 will be subject to the customer review and challenge procedures described in Sections 4, 5, and 6 of these Protocols. Section 4. Annual Review Procedures Each Annual Update shall be subject to the following review procedures ( Annual Review Procedures ): Page9of16 a. Interested Persons shall have up to the latest of one hundred fifty (150) calendar days after the Publication Date, thirty (30) calendar days after the receipt of all responses to timely submitted information requests (unless such period is extended with the written consent of Transource Missouri), or thirty (30) calendar days after resolution of a dispute that does not result in the production of additional information ( Review Period ), to review the calculations and to notify Transource Missouri in writing of any specific challenges, including challenges related to Accounting Changes, to the Annual Update ( Preliminary Challenge ). Transource Missouri shall promptly cause to be posted all Preliminary Challenges at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website and a link to the website will be electronically served upon the Service List. Transource Missouri shall respond in writing to a Preliminary Challenge within twenty (20) business days of receipt, and its response shall notify the challenging party of the extent to which Transource Missouri agrees or disagrees with the challenge. If Transource Missouri disagrees with the Preliminary Challenge, its response shall include supporting documentation. Transource Missouri shall promptly cause to be posted responses to all Preliminary Challenges at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website and a link to the website will be electronically served upon the Service List. b. Interested Persons shall have up to one hundred twenty (120) calendar days after each annual Publication Date (unless such period is extended with the written consent of Transource Missouri) to serve reasonable information requests on Transource Missouri. Information requests shall be limited to what is necessary to Page10of16 determine if: (i) Transource Missouri has properly calculated the Annual Update under review (including any corrections pursuant to Section 6); (ii) the costs included in the Annual Update are properly recordable and recorded, prudently incurred, and otherwise consistent with Transource Missouri s accounting policies, practices and procedures consistent with the USoA; (iii) the input data used in the Annual Update are accurate and correctly used in the Formula Rate; and (iv) the Formula Rate has been applied according to its terms, including the procedures in these Protocols. Information requests shall not solicit information concerning costs or allocations where the costs or allocation methods have been determined to be appropriate by FERC in the context of prior Transource Missouri Annual Updates, except that such information requests shall be permitted if they (i) seek to determine if there has been a change in circumstances, (ii) are in connection with corrections pursuant to Section 6, or (iii) relate to costs or allocations that have not previously been challenged and adjudicated by FERC. Information requests received will be posted at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website and a link to the website will be electronically served upon the Service List. c. Transource Missouri shall make a good faith effort to respond to information requests pertaining to the Annual Update within ten (10) business days of receipt of such requests. To the extent Transource Missouri and any Interested Person(s) are unable to resolve disputes related to information requests submitted in accordance with these Annual Review Procedures, Transource Missouri or any Interested Person may petition the FERC to appoint an Administrative Law Judge as a discovery Page11of16 master to resolve the discovery dispute(s) in accordance with these Protocols and consistent with the FERC s discovery rules. d. Preliminary Challenges, or Formal Challenges as described in Section 5 below, related to Accounting Changes shall be treated in the same manner under these Protocols as other challenges to the Annual Update. Failure to make a Preliminary Challenge with respect to an Accounting Change in an Annual Update shall not act as a bar with respect to a Formal Challenge with respect to that Annual Update, nor shall such failure bar a subsequent Preliminary Challenge related to a subsequent Annual Update to the extent such Accounting Change affects the subsequent Annual Update. e. If a change made by Transource Missouri to its accounting policies, practices or procedures, or the application of the Formula Rate, is found by the FERC to be unjust, unreasonable, and/or unduly discriminatory or preferential, then the calculation of the charges to be assessed during the Rate Year then under review, and the charges to be assessed during any subsequent Rate Years, including any True-up Adjustments, shall not include such change, but shall include any remedy that may be prescribed by FERC in the exercise of its discretion as of the effective date of such remedy, to ensure that the Formula Rate continues to operate in a manner that is just, reasonable, and not unduly discriminatory or preferential. Section 5. Resolution of Challenges a. If Transource Missouri and any Interested Person have not resolved any Preliminary Challenge to the Annual Update within sixty (60) calendar days after Page12of16 the end of the Review Period (unless such period is extended with the written consent of Transource Missouri to continue efforts to resolve the Preliminary Challenge), such Interested Person may, within thirty (30) calendar days thereafter, file a challenge with the FERC, pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 385.206 ( Formal Challenge ), which shall be served on Transource Missouri by electronic service on the date of such filing. Subject to any applicable confidentiality and Critical Energy Infrastructure Information restrictions, all information and correspondence produced by Transource Missouri pursuant to these Protocols may be included in any Formal Challenge or other FERC proceeding relating to the Formula Rate. b. Any response by Transource Missouri to a Formal Challenge must be submitted to the FERC within thirty (30) calendar days of the date of the filing of the Formal Challenge, and shall be served on the filing party(ies) and the Service List by electronic service on the date of such filing. c. In any proceeding concerning a given year s Annual Update (including corrections) or Accounting Change(s), Transource Missouri shall demonstrate the justness and reasonableness of the rate resulting from its application of the Formula Rate by demonstrating that it has reasonably and accurately calculated the Annual Update and/or reasonably adopted and applied the Accounting Change. d. Except as specifically provided herein, nothing herein shall be deemed to limit in any way the right of Transource Missouri to file unilaterally, pursuant to Section Page13of16 205 of the FPA and the regulations thereunder, an application seeking changes to the Formula Rate or to any of the stated value inputs requiring a Section 205 filing under these Protocols (including, but not limited to, ROE, depreciation and amortization rates, and PBOPs), or the right of any other party or the Commission to seek such changes pursuant to Section 206 of the FPA and the regulations thereunder. e. Transource Missouri may, at its discretion and at a time of its choosing, make a limited filing pursuant to Section 205 to modify stated values in the Formula Rate for amortization and depreciation rates, or PBOP rates. The sole issue in any such limited Section 205 proceeding shall be whether such proposed change(s) is just and reasonable, and it shall not address other aspects of the Formula Rate. Section 6. Changes to Annual Updates If Transource Missouri determines or concedes that corrections to the Annual Update are required, whether under Sections 4 or 5 of these Protocols, including but not limited to those requiring corrections to its FERC Form No. 1, or input data used for a Rate Year that would have affected the Annual Update for that Rate Year, Transource Missouri shall promptly notify the Service List, file a correction to the Annual Update with the FERC as an amended informational filing, and cause such information to be posted at a publicly accessible location on SPP s internet website. Such corrections shall be subject to review at the time they are made and shall be reflected in the next Annual Update, with interest. A corrected posting shall reset the deadlines under Section 4 and 5 of the Protocols for Interested Person review and the revised dates shall run from the posting date(s) for each of the corrections. The scope of review shall be limited to the aspects of the Formula Rate affected by the corrections. Interest on any over- or under- Page14of16 recovery due to corrections for preceding True-up Adjustments shall be calculated monthly on such over- or under-recovery from January 1 of the corrected Rate Year through December 31 of the Rate Year in which such over- or under-recovery is reflected ( Correction Period ). That is equivalent to two years interest applied to over- or under- collection. The applicable monthly interest rates for the Correction Period for an over-recovery shall be determined in accordance with the Formula Rate true-up worksheet divided by twelve (12) for each month from the beginning of the Correction Period through December 31 of the Rate Year immediately preceding the Rate Year in which such over-recovery is reflected. The applicable monthly interest rates for the Correction Period for an under-recovery shall be the annual interest rate determined in accordance 18 C.F.R 35.19a divided by twelve (12) for each month from the beginning of the Correction Period through December 31 of the Rate Year immediately preceding the Rate Year in which such under-recovery is reflected. Section 7. Construction Work in Progress a. Accounting. For each transmission project for which Transource Missouri has been authorized by a Commission order to include 100 percent of Construction Work in Progress ( CWIP ) in transmission rate base ( CWIP Incentive Project ), Transource Missouri shall use the following accounting procedures to ensure that it does not recover an Allowance for Funds Used During Construction ( AFUDC ) for such project. (i) Transource Missouri shall assign each CWIP Incentive Project a unique Funding Project Number ( FPN ) for internal cost tracking purposes. (ii) Transource Missouri shall record actual construction costs to each FPN through work orders that are coded to correspond to the FPN for each Page15of16 CWIP Incentive project. Such work orders shall be segregated from work orders for transmission projects for which the Commission has not authorized Transource Missouri to include CWIP in rate base. (iii) For each CWIP Incentive Project, Transource Missouri shall prepare monthly work order summaries of costs incurred under the associated FPN. These summaries shall show monthly additions to CWIP and plant in service and shall correspond to amounts recorded in Transource Missouri s FERC Form No. 1. Transource Missouri shall use these summaries as data inputs into the Annual Update calculated pursuant to Section 3. Transource Missouri shall make such work order summaries available upon request under the review procedures of Section 4. (iv) When a CWIP Incentive Project, or portion thereof, is placed into service, Transource Missouri shall deduct from total CWIP the accumulated charges for work orders under the FPN for that project, or portion thereof. The purpose of this control process is to ensure that expenditures are not double counted as both CWIP and as additions to plant. (v) For transmission projects for which the Commission has not authorized Transource Missouri to include CWIP in rate base, Transource Missouri shall record AFUDC to be applied to CWIP and capitalized when the project is placed into service. b. Annual Reporting. For each CWIP Incentive Project, Transource Missouri shall file a report with the Commission at the time of Transource Missouri s Annual Update that shall include the following information concerning each such project: Page16of16 (i) the actual amount of CWIP recorded for each project; (ii) any amounts recorded in related FERC accounts or subaccounts, such as AFUDC and regulatory liability; (iii) the resulting effect of CWIP on the revenue requirement; (iv) a statement of the current status of each project; and (v) the estimated in-service date for each project.

record_data.record_plain_text: AGREEMENT FOR THE LICENSING OF TRANSMISSION STRUCTURES KCP&L GREATER MISSOURI OPERATIONS COMPANY AND TRANSOURCE MISSOURI, LLC Tariff Submitter: Transource Missouri, LLC FERC Program Name: FERC FPA Electric Tariff Tariff Title: TMO Rate Schedules and Service Agreement Tariffs Tariff Proposed Effective Date: 01/01/2014 Tariff Record Title: Agreement for the Licensing of Transmission Structures Option Code: A Record Content Description: Pole Attachment Agreement Page 1 AGREEMENT FOR THE LICENSING OF TRANSMISSION STRUCTURES THIS AGREEMENT is entered into as of January 1, 2014 ( Effective Date ), between KCP&L Greater Missouri Operations Company, a Delaware corporation ( GMO ) and Transource Missouri, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ( Transource Missouri ). Background Information Transource Missouri operates or will construct certain transmission structures located along the west leg of the Iatan-Nashua 345 kV line as shown on the attached Exhibit A (the Structures ), which GMO desires to attach to and maintain transmission lines and appurtenant equipment (the Equipment ) upon. The parties hereto desire to set forth the terms and conditions upon which GMO will attach and maintain the Equipment on the Structures. Statement of Agreement The parties hereto acknowledge the accuracy of the above background information and in consideration of the terms and conditions described herein agree as follows: 1. SCOPE OF AGREEMENT. This Agreement sets forth the terms and conditions under which Transource Missouri shall license Structure space to GMO for the purpose of installing, maintaining, replacing and removing the Equipment. Such nonexclusive license shall be granted by Transource Missouri and such license shall be enjoyed by GMO in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. Unless otherwise set forth herein, all Structures licensed hereunder shall be and remain the property of Transource Missouri regardless of any payment by GMO toward their cost. No use, however extended, of the Structures or payment of any fee or charge required hereunder shall create or vest in GMO any claim of right, possession, title, or interest in the Structures. 2. DEFINITIONS. For the purpose of this Agreement, certain terms shall have the meanings given in this paragraph as follows: a. Design Requirements Transource Missouri s reasonable internal standards, generally accepted industry standards, the National Electrical Safety Code, and any other applicable regulations or codes promulgated by any federal, state, local or other governmental authority having jurisdiction. b. Joint Use - The simultaneous use of a structure for the attachment of both parties. c. Proposal - A standardized form used by the parties to communicate the respective needs, requirements, and intentions regarding proposed Joint Use. Page 2 d. Total Cost - All material, labor and applicable administrative overheads. e. Transfer Notice - A standardized form used by the parties to communicate that a new structure placement has been completed and it is time for the licensee to relocate their facilities to the new structure. 3. STRUCTURE ADDITIONAL ATTACHMENT LICENSES. Whenever GMO desires to reserve space on a Structure in addition to space utilized by the Equipment in place on the effective date of this agreement it shall submit a Proposal therefor, specifying the location of the Structure in question, the amount of space desired, a detailed description of the equipment to be attached, the final sag of any wire facilities, and the stringing tension of any wireline facilities. Transource Missouri shall then decide, in its reasonable discretion, whether to license space on the Structure for the proposed attachment of the additional equipment. If Transource Missouri grants permission to attach, then after the completion by Transource Missouri of any transferring or rearranging, which in Transource Missouri's judgment is then required with respect to the equipment, including any necessary Structure replacements, GMO may use said space for the attachment of the equipment in the manner specified in said Proposal and in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. 4. STANDARDS FOR INSTALLATION. The Equipment shall be installed in a manner satisfactory to Transource Missouri and so as not to interfere with the present or any reasonably considered use which Transource Missouri may desire to make of the Structures. All Equipment shall be installed and at all times maintained by GMO so as to comply with the Design Requirements. It is understood and agreed between the parties hereto that at all times during the term of this Agreement the parties shall consider all electric wires to be energized and that working in the vicinity of the wires poses potential dangers. Both parties shall warn all of their employees, agents, contractors and subcontractors, or any other parties who may be working on behalf of the parties hereto, of the potential dangers. 5. EMERGENCY CONDITIONS. If Transource Missouri is unable to respond in a timely manner to an emergency condition where Structure replacement is necessary, then GMO shall be permitted to replace the Structure. Where GMO must replace Transource Missouri s structure under emergency conditions, GMO may require Transource Missouri to pay GMO for the Total Cost incurred in replacing the Structure, including the cost of removal/disposal of the old Structure. 6. REARRANGEMENT. The parties shall rearrange their facilities in order to reasonably accommodate the needs of the other party. The party making such rearrangement request shall be responsible for all costs associated with such rearrangements. 7. HAZARD. Whenever Transource Missouri notifies GMO in writing that in Transource Missouri's reasonable judgment the continued operation of the Equipment constitutes a hazard to the service rendered by Transource Missouri, is dangerous to employees of Transource Missouri or of such other persons or the public, or otherwise fails to comply with the Design Requirements, GMO shall remove, rearrange or change the Equipment in compliance with the Design Requirements within ten (10) days of receipt of such notice. In case of an emergency, which in Transource Missouri's reasonable judgment requires Transource Missouri to immediately remove or relocate the GMO Facilities, Transource Missouri reserves the right to remove or relocate such GMO Facilities as required, at GMO's expense. Page 3 8. RELOCATION OF STRUCTURES. Whenever it is necessary to replace or change the location of a Structure, Transource Missouri shall, before making such change, give reasonable notice thereof to GMO, by use of a Transfer Notice, specifying in such notice the time of the proposed replacement or change. GMO shall arrange to transfer the Equipment within the time specified. If GMO does not transfer its facilities within the time specified by Transource Missouri, then Transource Missouri may transfer the facilities and GMO shall pay the Total Cost of such transfer. 9. ABANDONMENT OF STRUCTURES. Prior to the abandonment of any Structure, Transource Missouri shall provide written notice to GMO of such planned abandonment and, provided Transource Missouri is not required to sell the Structure to a third party, permit GMO to purchase any such abandoned Structures at net book value. If GMO does not respond to Transource Missouri in writing within ten (10) days that it wishes to purchase such abandoned Structures, then Transource Missouri may assume GMO is not interested in purchasing the abandoned Structures and proceed with their disposal. In the event of the sale of the Structures to GMO, GMO shall assume sole responsibility for any and all liability, cost or expense arising thereafter out of the location, use, condition or disposal of said Structure. GMO may, at any time, abandon the use of a Structure hereunder, but only by removing therefrom all of the Equipment and by giving written notice thereof to Transource Missouri. 10. THIRD PARTY ATTACHMENTS. Upon GMO s written consent, which consent shall not be unreasonably denied or delayed, Transource Missouri also may grant to third parties, by contract or otherwise, rights or privileges to use any structures covered by this Agreement. Transource Missouri shall have the right to the entirety of any payments from such third party. Any such third party attachments must comply with the conditions established in the Standards For Installation Article set forth above. If there is insufficient space on a Structure to accommodate third party attachments, the third party shall be required to reimburse Transource Missouri and GMO for all costs incurred by them in making such space available, including transfer costs if relocation to a new Structure is made necessary by the attachment of a third party. Each party shall, to the extent such information is available, upon the request of the other party furnish to such other party a list of the names, addresses, phone numbers and representatives of each person licensing or leasing space on its poles, conduits and appurtenant facilities for the attachment of third party facilities. Such party does not warrant the accuracy or completeness of any such information provided, and to the extent locations of attachments and/or locations of facilities are described or shown, such locations of attachments and locations of facilities are described or shown in their approximate locations. 11. RENTAL FEES. The base rent ( Base Rent ) shall be $125 per month for the use of each Structure. The resulting annual Base Rent for all 23 Structures shall be $34,500. The parties have calculated such Base Rent based upon on the present value of the annual cost avoided by GMO due to the reduction of rate base associated with the early retirement of previously existing transmission structures displaced by the Iatan-Nashua 345 kV line. The attachment rates also reflect the related decrease in GMO maintenance expense. Page 4 In the event that any of the 23 Structures and appurtenant facilities owned and used by Transource Missouri that support the operation of the Equipment is replaced in whole or in part during the term of this contract, the Base Rent shall be supplemented to reflect the additional investment in accordance with the following formula: Total Rent = Base Rent + Supplemental Rent Supplemental Rent = Replacement Cost x Fixed Charge Rate x 2nd Line Percentage Where: Replacement Cost = Cost of replacing the Structure and/or appurtenant facilities, net of any insurance proceeds that may be received for property loss. Replacement Cost shall be incurred only in accordance with good utility practice and with no mark-up for profit and the replacement component(s) shall be of a type and design generally accepted and required for such function. Fixed Charge Rate = 11 percent, which is the levelized rate to be applied to determine an annual cost of the replacement component. 2nd Line Percentage = 40 percent, which is the estimated portion of the cost of the 23 structures that results from construction of the jointly used segment to accommodate two 345 kV lines rather than one line. GMO shall commence paying the Supplemental Rent upon the in-service date of replacement of any of the 23 Structures and/or appurtenant facilities owned and used by Transource Missouri to support operation of the Equipment. Total Rent shall be paid annually in arrears by the end of each calendar year. Transource Missouri shall prorate any partial Base Rent or Supplemental Rent. As consideration for the rent paid herein, Transource Missouri shall be responsible for the entire cost of maintaining the Structures and any required vegetation management in accordance with the Design Requirements. 12. TIME OF PAYMENT. Payments of amounts due hereunder are due on the dates or at the times indicated with respect to each such payment. In the event the time for any payment is not specified, such payment shall be due thirty (30) days from the date of receipt of invoice therefor. 13. EASEMENTS. The parties hereto shall cooperate with each other to resolve any landowner disputes, which may arise concerning the presence of the Equipment or the Structures. The licenses granted hereunder are granted without warranties or representations concerning Transource Missouri s real property rights to operate the Structures. GMO s right to license Structure space shall terminate upon a reasonable determination by Transource Missouri that Transource Missouri no longer has the necessary real property rights to continue to operate the Structures. Upon such termination GMO shall have the option of either removing the Equipment from any affected Structure or purchasing such affected Structures at net book value. Page 5 14. DEFAULT OR NONCOMPLIANCE. If either party shall be in material breach of any of its obligations under this Agreement and such party fails to cure such breach within thirty (30) days after receiving written notice thereof from the other party, the party not in default may, without releasing any other legal remedies available to it, terminate this Agreement by providing six (6) months prior written notice. 15. TERM OF AGREEMENT. Except as provided in the Default Or Noncompliance Article, this Agreement shall commence upon the Effective Date and shall continue for an initial term expiring on the first December 31 following the thirtieth anniversary of the commencement date. Neither party shall be considered in default in the performance of its obligations herein, or any of them, to the extent that performance is delayed or prevented due to the following causes which are beyond the control of said party: Acts of God or the public enemy, war, revolution, terrorism, civil commotion, blockade or embargo, fires, explosions, cyclones, floods, unavoidable casualties, quarantine or any other cause beyond the control of said party. 17. GOVERNING LAW. Except insofar as governed by federal law, this Agreement shall be construed in accordance with, and its performance shall be governed by, applicable laws in effect in the State of Missouri. 18. EXECUTION. This Agreement may be executed in two counterparts each of which so executed shall be deemed to be an original. 19. MODIFICATIONS OF AGREEMENT. This Agreement and its Exhibits constitute the entire agreement between the parties respecting structure GMO Facilities. 20. PRESERVATION OF REMEDIES. No delay or omission in the exercise of any power or remedy herein provided or otherwise available to a party shall impair or affect that party s right thereafter to exercise the same. 21. NOTICES. Any notice from one party to another under this Agreement shall be a written notice sent by the United States mail, certified mail, with return receipt requested and postage prepaid, or by a nationally recognized overnight courier (e.g., Federal Express), with proof of delivery. In an emergency situation, notice may be provided by facsimile transmission followed by written notice as set forth above. Notice to Transource shall be addressed as follows: Transource Missouri, LLC Attn: President 1 Riverside Plaza Columbus, Ohio 43215 Page 6 Notice to GMO shall be addressed as follows: Kansas City Power & Light Company Resource Management, F&M Attn: Contract Administrator PO Box 418679 Kansas City, Missouri 64141-9679 Each party may change its address or designated representative for purposes of this section at any time by written notice to the other party. 22. OPPORTUNITY TO CURE. Unless otherwise set forth herein, both parties shall be provided an opportunity to cure defaults hereunder pursuant to the terms of this Section 22. In the event of a default, the party declaring such default shall notify the defaulting party in writing describing the nature of the default and shall provide the defaulting party an opportunity to cure such default within thirty (30) days of such notice, or if both parties agree that the cure of the default requires a period in excess of thirty (30) days, the defaulting party shall commence, in good faith, activities required to effect a cure and diligently prosecute such activities. 23. SUBLICENSING AND ASSIGNMENT. Neither party shall assign this Agreement to a successor without the consent of the other party, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. GMO shall not sublicense or sublease any rights conferred herein without the consent of Transource Missouri, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. 24. HEADINGS. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Transource Missouri shall not be responsible for any liability or loss resulting from the negligence of GMO. Preliminary Development Agreement between Transource Missouri, LLC, and Evergy Missouri West, Inc.
(Mullin Creek 1) (SPP-GEN-2024-028)
Tariff Submitter: Transource Missouri, LLC FERC Tariff Program Name: FERC FPA Electric Tariff Tariff Title: TMO Tariff Database Tariff Record Proposed Effective Date: 08/12/2025 Description: Rate Schedule No. 141 Tariff Record Title: TMO-Evergy Missouri West (Mullin Creek 1) PDA Option Code: A
PRELIMINARY DEVELOPMENT AGREEMENT
This Preliminary Development Agreement (the Agreement) is entered into as of August 12, 2025 (the Execution Date) between Transource Missouri, LLC, a Delaware corporation (Transource) and Evergy Missouri West, Inc., a Delaware corporation (Generator). Transource and Generator may be referred to individually as a Party and collectively as the Parties.
RECITALS
A. Generator is in the process of developing certain generation assets in Nodaway County, Missouri with a proposed nameplate capacity of 460.2 MW (the Plant or Mullin Creek 1).
B. The Southwest Power Pool (SPP) is conducting an Interconnection Facilities Study (Facilities Study) in response to Generators Generation Interconnection Request #GEN- 2024-028 to SPP to interconnect the Plant. It is anticipated the Plant would be interconnected to the Transource system. The completed Facilities Study will identify certain interconnection facilities necessary or appropriate to enable interconnection service to Generator for the Plant (the Interconnection Facilities).
C. The Parties anticipate entering into an SPP standard Generation Interconnection Agreement (the GIA) and possibly an Interim Generation Interconnection Agreement (the Interim GIA) in advance of the GIA that will, among other things, address the engineering, procurement, and construction of the Interconnection Facilities.
D. Generator has requested that Transource perform certain preliminary planning, engineering, design, and procurement activities related to the proposed interconnection prior to the execution of the GIA or Interim GIA by the Parties. Transource is willing to do so on the terms and conditions set out in this Agreement.
AGREEMENTS
NOW, THEREFORE, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
1. DEFINITIONS; RULES OF CONSTRUCTION
1.1. Definitions. As used in this Agreement, terms defined in Exhibit 1.1 have the meanings set forth therein.
1.2. Rules of Construction. Unless the context of this Agreement requires otherwise, the plural includes the singular, and the singular includes the plural. The words include, includes and including are not limiting and have the inclusive meaning of including without limitation. The words hereof, herein, hereby, hereunder and other similar terms of this Agreement refer to this Agreement as a whole and not exclusively to any particular provision of this Agreement. All pronouns and any variations thereof will be deemed to refer to masculine, feminine, or neuter, singular, or plural, as the identity of the Person or Persons may require. Unless otherwise expressly provided, any agreement, instrument, or Applicable Law defined or referred
Preliminary Development Agreement, GEN-2024-028 Page 1
to herein means such agreement or instrument or Applicable Law as from time to time amended, modified, or supplemented, including (in the case of agreements or instruments) by waiver or consent and (in the case of Applicable Law) by succession of comparable successor law and includes (in the case of agreements or instruments) references to all attachments thereto and instruments incorporated therein. A reference to a Party includes its successors and permitted assigns. This Agreement is the result of negotiations between, and has been reviewed by, the Parties, and their respective counsel have had the opportunity to review this Agreement. Accordingly, this Agreement shall be deemed to be the product of all Parties hereto, and no ambiguity shall be construed in favor of or against any Party.
2. EFFECTIVE DATE; COMMENCEMENT DATE; TERMINATION
2.1. Commencement of Work. Transource shall become obligated to commence the Work hereunder when both the Effective Date has occurred in accordance with Section 2.2 and the Commencement Date has occurred in accordance with Section 2.3.
2.2. Effective Date. Transource shall file this Agreement with FERC, and Generator agrees to cooperate with Transource and provide reasonable assistance to Transource in such filing and proceedings related thereto. This Agreement shall become effective on the date specified by FERC (Effective Date). However, if FERC or any other Governmental Authority suspends this Agreement or any part thereof, institutes an investigation or proceeding with respect to this Agreement or any other agreement referred to or contemplated by this Agreement, or imposes any conditions, limitation or qualifications which individually or in the aggregate are determined by Transource or Generator to be adverse to it, then either Transource or Generator may terminate this Agreement upon written notice to the other Party.
2.3. Commencement Date. The commencement date shall be the date on which each of the following events shall have occurred or been waived by the Parties (Commencement Date):
2.3.1. Receipt by both Parties of all necessary Governmental Approvals (in form and substance reasonably satisfactory to each of the Parties) in addition to the Governmental Approval specified in Section 2.2 hereof.
2.3.2. Transources receipt of any Security described in Section 4.2 and any replacements or increases thereto.
If, at the request of Generator, Transource waives a condition specified in this Section 2.3 so that Work can proceed, Transource will be entitled to reimbursement of costs pursuant to this Agreement as if the Work had been performed only after satisfaction of the waived condition.
2.4. Events of Termination. This Agreement may be terminated by the Parties as follows:
2.4.1. This Agreement may be terminated by mutual written agreement of the Parties.
2.4.2. This Agreement will terminate upon execution of the GIA or Interim GIA, if applicable, by the Parties, and any further measures with respect to the Work will be undertaken pursuant to the GIA or Interim GIA.
Preliminary Development Agreement GEN-2024-028 Page 2
2.4.3. Generator may terminate this Agreement for convenience on ten (10) days advance written notice to the other Party.
2.4.4. Either Party may terminate this Agreement as provided in Sections 2.2, 5.1, and 6.2.
2.4.5. Transource may terminate this Agreement on written notice to Generator if Generator has not executed a GIA or Interim GIA for the Plant with Transource by June 14, 2029.
2.4.6. Either Party may terminate this Agreement if any Governmental Authority denies approval of any necessary or appropriate approvals for the Work or the Plant, or if any Governmental Authority shall have issued an order, decree, ruling, or other action restraining, enjoining, or otherwise prohibiting such Partys performance of this Agreement or its contemplated ownership or operation of the Plant or Interconnection Facilities.
2.5. Regulatory Approval of Termination. Any termination of this Agreement provided for herein shall be subject to any necessary approval by FERC or any other Governmental Authority, as applicable.
2.6. Survival of Rights; Merger into GIA.
2.6.1. Subject to Section 2.6.2, termination of this Agreement shall not relieve the Parties of obligations that by their nature should survive such termination, including, without limitation, payment obligations, remedies, indemnification obligations, confidentiality and any provisions of this Agreement that explicitly provide for survival after termination.
2.6.2. If the Parties execute a GIA or Interim GIA, then, except as otherwise provided in the GIA or Interim GIA, all of the rights and obligations of the Parties with respect to the Work will be merged into and controlled exclusively by the GIA or Interim GIA, and the provisions of this Agreement will have no continuing force or effect; provided, however, that any amount payable hereunder that does not become part of the amounts payable under the GIA or Interim GIA will continue to be subject to invoicing and payment (including application of the Security) under this Agreement.
2.7. Termination Costs. If a Party elects to terminate this Agreement pursuant to Article 2.4 above (other than pursuant to Section 2.4.2), Generator shall pay all costs incurred by Transource for the Work performed hereunder (including any cancellation costs relating to orders or contracts for materials and equipment procured hereunder), as of the date the non-terminating Party receives notice of the termination (Termination Date). In the event of termination by any Party, Transource shall use commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate the costs, damages and charges arising as a consequence of
Preliminary Development Agreement GEN-2024-028 Page 3
termination. Upon termination of this Agreement (other than pursuant to Section 2.4.2), unless otherwise ordered or approved by FERC:
2.7.1. Transource shall, to the extent possible, and with Generator's authorization cancel any pending orders of, or return, any materials or equipment procured hereunder; provided that in the event Generator elects not to authorize such cancellation, Generator shall assume all payment obligations with respect to such materials, equipment, and contracts, and Transource shall deliver such material and equipment, and, if necessary, assign such orders, to Generator as soon as practicable, at Generator's expense. If Generator does not provide its authorization to cancel pending orders within three (3) Business Days of the termination date, the Generator shall be deemed to have authorized cancellation of all pending orders and return of materials and equipment.
2.7.2. Except as specifically provided in this Section, Generator shall be responsible for all costs incurred in association with the Work incurred up to the date of the Termination Date, including any cancellation costs relating to orders or contracts for materials and equipment, and other expenses for which Transource has incurred expenses and has not been reimbursed by Generator.
2.7.3. If Generator chooses not to accept delivery of materials or, equipment procured hereunder Generator shall be responsible for all costs associated with procuring such materials and equipment to the extent that Transource determines that it would not able to utilize such materials, equipment or facilities or that it would not be able to recover the costs for such materials, equipment or facilities in its rates. To the extent that Generator has already paid Transource for any or all such costs of materials or equipment not taken by Generator and Transource is able to utilize such materials or equipment and recover their costs in rates, Transource shall refund such amounts to Generator, less any costs including penalties incurred by Transource to cancel any pending orders or return such materials or equipment. Such refund, if any, will occur upon final reconciliation of project costs pursuant to Section 4.1.3.
3. PRELIMINARY DEVELOPMENT WORK
3.1. Scope of Work. Transource will undertake, directly or through its affiliates or contractors (or any combination thereof), the performance of the work described in Schedule 3.1 and any attachments referenced therein (the Work).
3.2. Modification of the Work. Because the Work has been specified in this Agreement prior to the completion of the Facilities Study relating to the Plant, the Parties acknowledge that the specification of the Work and the estimates of its cost set out in this Agreement are not binding on Transource and that Transource may modify Schedule 3.1 to reflect the results of the Facilities Study on written notice to Generator.
3.3. Generators Technical Information. Generator will provide relevant information to Transource concerning the Plant and the Work as requested by Transource from time to time.
Preliminary Development Agreement GEN-2024-028 Page 4
Generator represents that any technical or engineering information, reports, drawings, data, specifications, analyses, and other similar materials previously or hereafter provided to Transource or to SPP by Generator or Generators contractors or consultants in connection with the Plant or the Work has been and will be prepared in accordance with Good Utility Practice and that Generator is not aware of any reason to distrust the accuracy and completeness of such information and materials.
3.4. Disclaimer of Warranty. Transource will perform the Work consistent with Applicable Law, applicable Governmental Approvals, and Good Utility Practice. Except for the foregoing, Transource HEREBY DISCLAIMS ALL EXPRESS OR IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR GOOD AND WORKMANLIKE PERFORMANCE. THE FOREGOING STANDARDS FOR PERFORMANCE OF THIS AGREEMENT WILL BE MERGED INTO THE GIA AS PROVIDED IN SECTION 2.6, AND THE ONLY WARRANTIES WITH RESPECT TO THE WORK WILL THEREUPON BE THOSE PROVIDED BY THE GIA.
3.5. Progress Reports. On a monthly basis, Transource will update Generator on progress of the Work.
3.6. Schedule. The Parties will exercise commercially reasonable efforts to perform the Work on a schedule that would enable the Parties to achieve a targeted back feed date for the Generator facilities, including construction under the future GIA or Interim GIA, on or before 06/01/2029.
3.6.1. Execute this Agreement 8-12-2025
3.6.2. Engineering, Project Management, Long Lead Material Payment Due Date, Referenced in 4.1.2.(a)
3.6.3. Engineering, Project Management, Remaining Procurement Payment Amount Due Date, Referenced in 4.1.2.(b)
3.6.4. Interim GIA Execution or execution of another form of agreement providing for construction of the Transmission Owner Interconnect Facilities and/or Network Upgrades prior to execution of an Interim GIA or GIA, as applicable 01-15-2028
4. COSTS
4.1. Responsibility for Costs; Initial Payments; Final Reconciliation.
4.1.1. Generator will bear all costs of the Work (including any modifications thereto) except to the extent that the Parties agree otherwise in the GIA or Interim GIA. Costs to be borne by the Generator for the Work under this Agreement will include all costs, charges, and expenses incurred by Transource in connection with the Work, including the costs of materials, equipment, and supplies from third parties, the costs of materials and equipment withdrawn from Transources internal inventories (or those of its affiliates), transportation and storage costs, internal payroll and payroll
Preliminary Development Agreement GEN-2024-028 Page 5
loading factors, travel expenses, overhead factors, other internal costs, the costs to acquire land rights, third party expenses, sales and use taxes, and fees and costs for Governmental Approvals.
4.1.2. Generator shall make two payments to Transource as follows:
(a) Within thirty (30) Business Days after this Agreement is filed at FERC, Transource shall issue an invoice to Generator for $2,500,000 for the engineering and design portion of the Work described in Schedule 3.1. Generator shall make the payment to Transource according to the due date on the invoice. Transource shall not be obligated to commence any portion of the engineering and design work until it receives the foregoing payment.
(b) Within seven months after the Execution Date, Transource shall issue an invoice to Generator for $2,000,000 for the procurement portion of the Work described in Schedule 3.1. Generator shall make the payment to Transource according to the due date on the invoice. Transource shall not be obligated to commence any procurement activities until it receives the foregoing payment.
4.1.3. Upon completion of the Work, Transource shall submit an invoice to Generator for the total costs of the Work under this Agreement, and Generator shall pay such costs to the extent they exceed the initial payment of $4,500,000. Such invoice shall include any income tax gross-up that may result under Applicable Law if income tax is payable by Transource with respect to payments by Generator to Transource, and such invoice will be payable in full, without offset, abatement, or reduction for any reason, within thirty (30) Calendar Days of the date of invoice. If Generator in good faith disputes any portion of an invoice, Generator will (i) explain the basis for the dispute in writing to Transource within fifteen (15) Calendar Days of the date of the invoice and (ii) without prejudice to its claim for refund of any disputed amount, pay the entire portion of the invoiced amount on or before the due date stated on the invoice.
4.2. Information Concerning Costs. PRELIMINARY DEVELOPMENT AGREEMENT
This Preliminary Development Agreement (the Agreement) is entered into as of August 15, 2025 (the Execution Date) between Transource Missouri, LLC, a Delaware corporation (Transource) and Evergy Metro, Inc., a Delaware corporation (Generator). Transource and Generator may be referred to individually as a Party and collectively as the Parties.
RECITALS
A. Generator is in the process of developing certain generation assets in Nodaway County, Missouri with a proposed nameplate capacity of 460.2 MW (the Plant or Mullin Creek 2).
B. The Southwest Power Pool (SPP) is conducting an Interconnection Facilities Study (Facilities Study) in response to Generators Generation Interconnection Request #GEN- 2024-053 to SPP to interconnect the Plant. It is anticipated the Plant would be interconnected to the Transource system. The completed Facilities Study will identify certain interconnection facilities necessary or appropriate to enable interconnection service to Generator for the Plant (the Interconnection Facilities).
C. The Parties anticipate entering into an SPP standard Generation Interconnection Agreement (the GIA) and possibly an Interim Generation Interconnection Agreement (the Interim GIA) in advance of the GIA that will, among other things, address the engineering, procurement, and construction of the Interconnection Facilities.
D. Generator has requested that Transource perform certain preliminary planning, engineering, design, and procurement activities related to the proposed interconnection prior to the execution of the GIA or Interim GIA by the Parties. Transource is willing to do so on the terms and conditions set out in this Agreement.
AGREEMENTS
NOW, THEREFORE, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
1. DEFINITIONS; RULES OF CONSTRUCTION
1.1. Definitions. As used in this Agreement, terms defined in Exhibit 1.1 have the meanings set forth therein.
1.2. Rules of Construction. Unless the context of this Agreement requires otherwise, the plural includes the singular, and the singular includes the plural. Unless otherwise expressly provided, any agreement, instrument, or Applicable Law defined or referred
Preliminary Development Agreement, GEN-2024-053 Page 1
to herein means such agreement or instrument or Applicable Law as from time to time amended, modified, or supplemented, including (in the case of agreements or instruments) by waiver or consent and (in the case of Applicable Law) by succession of comparable successor law and includes (in the case of agreements or instruments) references to all attachments thereto and instruments incorporated therein. A reference to a Party includes its successors and permitted assigns. This Agreement is the result of negotiations between, and has been reviewed by, the Parties, and their respective counsel have had the opportunity to review this Agreement. Accordingly, this Agreement shall be deemed to be the product of all Parties hereto, and no ambiguity shall be construed in favor of or against any Party.
2. EFFECTIVE DATE; COMMENCEMENT DATE; TERMINATION
2.1. Commencement of Work. Transource shall become obligated to commence the Work hereunder when both the Effective Date has occurred in accordance with Section 2.2 and the Commencement Date has occurred in accordance with Section 2.3.

Transource shall file this Agreement with FERC, and Generator agrees to cooperate with Transource and provide reasonable assistance to Transource in such filing and proceedings related thereto. 2.3.1. Receipt by both Parties of all necessary Governmental Approvals (in form and substance reasonably satisfactory to each of the Parties) in addition to the Governmental Approval specified in Section 2.2 hereof.
2.3.2. Transources receipt of any Security described in Section 4.2 and any replacements or increases thereto.

2.4.1. This Agreement may be terminated by mutual written agreement of the Parties.
2.4.2. This Agreement will terminate upon execution of the GIA or Interim GIA, if applicable, by the Parties, and any further measures with respect to the Work will be undertaken pursuant to the GIA or Interim GIA.

2.4.3. Generator may terminate this Agreement for convenience on ten (10) days advance written notice to the other Party.
2.4.4. Either Party may terminate this Agreement as provided in Sections 2.2, 5.1, and 6.2.
2.4.5. Transource may terminate this Agreement on written notice to Generator if Generator has not executed a GIA or Interim GIA for the Plant with Transource by June 16, 2030.
2.4.6. Either Party may terminate this Agreement if any Governmental Authority denies approval of any necessary or appropriate approvals for the Work or the Plant, or if any Governmental Authority shall have issued an order, decree, ruling, or other action restraining, enjoining, or otherwise prohibiting such Partys performance of this Agreement or its contemplated ownership or operation of the Plant or Interconnection Facilities.

Subject to Section 2.6.2, termination of this Agreement shall not relieve the Parties of obligations that by their nature should survive such termination, including, without limitation, payment obligations, remedies, indemnification obligations, confidentiality and any provisions of this Agreement that explicitly provide for survival after termination.

2.7.3. Such refund, if any, will occur upon final reconciliation of project costs pursuant to Section 4.1.3.
3. PRELIMINARY DEVELOPMENT WORK
3.1. Scope of Work. Transource will undertake, directly or through its affiliates or contractors (or any combination thereof), the performance of the work described in Schedule 3.1 and any attachments referenced therein (the Work).
3.2. Modification of the Work. Because the Work has been specified in this Agreement prior to the completion of the Facilities Study relating to the Plant, the Parties acknowledge that the specification of the Work and the estimates of its cost set out in this Agreement are not binding on Transource and that Transource may modify Schedule 3.1 to reflect the results of the Facilities Study on written notice to Generator.
